(127, 1, '2013-06-06 06:43:24', '2013-06-06 06:43:24', '<p>Mike is a professional speaker that puts his actions before his words. Rather than talking about what he has done or been through, Mike talks about what he''s doing.</p>\r\n <p>He specializes in speaking to students and professionals about topics like bullying, substance abuse, leadership and pursuing passions. Having worked with youth for more than a decade, Mike has founded and continues to direct two nationally-recognized non-profit organizations (the BAY and Skate for Change). Red Bull, TEDX (TED conferences), State Farm and people like Ryan Sheckler have taken notice of his reckless pursuit to help the disadvantaged. Maybe it''s time you take a look, too. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>He''s passionate. He''s real. He loves people. But most of all, he motivates others to live better lives. </p>\r\n\r\n', 'Mike Smith', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'mike-smith', '', '', '2013-06-27 08:17:13', '2013-06-27 08:17:13', '', 0, 'http://biziindia.com/finaospeakers/?post_type=speakers&#038;p=127', 0, 'speakers', '', 2),
(129, 1, '2013-06-06 06:38:19', '2013-06-06 06:38:19', 'Mike Smith – Youth motivational speaker – speaks to North Thurston students about making a better life for others. Mike Smith is a professional inspirational speaker based out of Lincoln Nebraska, He specializes in speaking to students and professionals about topics like bullying, substance abuse, leadership and pursuing passions. He is the founder of the Bay, a non –profit skate park in Nebraska and a Skate for Change foundation. He has been featured by Red Bull, TEDX(TED conferences) and State Farm. North Thurston students found his presentation- highly inspirational, motivating and engaging. Here are some reviews from students at NTHS\n\nBrooklyn Falter – thought he connected well with students in high school and how students can change the climate in your school by making a difference for one person at a time. She liked what Mike said about getting out of your comfort zone and thinking about the legacy you want to leave behind at your school.\n\nSamantha Minor – thought Mike was very inspiring and that the story of his high school experience really connected and resonated with student here at NTHS.\n', 'Mike Smith', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '127-revision', '', '', '2013-06-06 06:38:19', '2013-06-06 06:38:19', '', 127, 'http://biziindia.com/finaospeakers/127-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(130, 1, '2013-06-06 06:43:24', '2013-06-06 06:43:24', 'Mike Smith – Youth motivational speaker – speaks to North Thurston students about making a better life for others. Mike Smith is a professional inspirational speaker based out of Lincoln Nebraska, He specializes in speaking to students and professionals about topics like bullying, substance abuse, leadership and pursuing passions. He is the founder of the Bay, a non –profit skate park in Nebraska and a Skate for Change foundation. He has been featured by Red Bull, TEDX(TED conferences) and State Farm. North Thurston students found his presentation- highly inspirational, motivating and engaging. Here are some reviews from students at NTHS\r\n\r\nBrooklyn Falter – thought he connected well with students in high school and how students can change the climate in your school by making a difference for one person at a time. She liked what Mike said about getting out of your comfort zone and thinking about the legacy you want to leave behind at your school.\r\n\r\nSamantha Minor – thought Mike was very inspiring and that the story of his high school experience really connected and resonated with student here at NTHS.\r\n', 'Mike Smith', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '127-revision-2', '', '', '2013-06-06 06:43:24', '2013-06-06 06:43:24', '', 127, 'http://biziindia.com/finaospeakers/127-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(131, 1, '2013-06-06 06:30:57', '2013-06-06 06:30:57', 'Conference Keynote/Assembly Presentation:\r\nBe a Catalyst\r\nScott’s presentations begin as a giant party. In one moment, students are laughing hysterically, moving actively on their feet, and shouting “ROCK ON!” at the top of their lungs. Yet only minutes later, that same room is silent; students find themselves hanging on to every word of Scott’s heartfelt and challenging message. It is at this point that the students in attendance realize they are no longer watching a presentation to an audience of hundreds or even thousands—they are hearing their own personal call to action.\r\n\r\n“Scott is different because he doesn’t demand anything. He simply asks students what they should be demanding from themselves and from each other… getting them to aspire to a higher calling, a higher purpose.  Scott’s speech laid the groundwork for our entire leadership program.”\r\n- Craig Sutphin, Director of Student Leadership, St. Mary’s HS, Berkeley, CA\r\n\r\nScott gets that students have a HUGE impact on those around them—from their casual acquaintances at school to the close friends they see virtually 24/7. Each and every student has the power to influence their world in some way, shape, or form. Before changing anything, though, each student must undoubtedly recognize that the world in which they live is not perfect by any means. It takes passion and determination to make it a better place.\r\nRegardless of the situation, capacity, or context, the only way students will truly change their circumstances is if they decide to be a catalyst—someone who changes the status quo.\r\n\r\nPast Speech Topics / Workshops Include\r\nRespect\r\nSchool Spirit\r\nIssue Awareness\r\nStandardized Testing\r\nFreshman Orientation\r\nSenior Institute Days\r\nBullying\r\nPublic Speaking\r\nStudent Activity Planning\r\nand many more…\r\n\r\n', 'Scott Backovich', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '119-revision-3', '', '', '2013-06-06 06:30:57